title: Gay Dad - 2 Albums.zip
description:
Gay Dad were one of the last UK Britpop bands to be launched in the late 1990s. They generated massive news media interest and had moderate chart success, but they failed to sustain their popularity and broke up in 2002. The original line-up consisted of Cliff Jones (guitarist/vocalist), James Riseboro (keyboardist), Nigel Hoyle (bassist), Charley Stone (guitarist) and Nicholas "Baz" Crowe (drummer). They released 2 albums.

Albums

    * Leisure Noise (1999)
    * Transmission (2001)
